  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Treatment outcomes of lymphoblastic lymphoma (LBL) have improved by the use of the regimens
      for acute lymphoblastic leukemia. Hyper-CVAD is one of the most effective treatments with
      high remission rate in acute lymphoblastic leukemia (ALL) and LBL. However, the treatment
      outcome of hyper-CVAD in LBL has reported only in small number of patients from single
      institution. The investigators conducted this study to evaluate the hyper-CVAD regimen based
      treatment in LBL.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      We will analyze treatment outcome of lymphoblastic lymphoma patients treated with hyper-CVAD
      regimen from 13 institutions in Korea. In all patients, hyper-CVAD was initial treatment.
      After achievement of response, patients either underwent hematopoietic stem cell
      transplantation (HSCT) or consolidation with hyper-CVAD.
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
